title: Readout of Vice President Biden’s Meeting with Israeli President Reuven Rivlin | whitehouse.gov
content:
The White House
Office of the Vice President


For Immediate Release
March 09, 2016

 



Readout of Vice President Biden’s Meeting with Israeli President Reuven Rivlin





	The Vice President met today with Israeli President Reuven Rivlin in Jerusalem. The two leaders discussed a number of the regional security challenges facing the Middle East, including in Syria, Iraq, Yemen, and Libya. The Vice President also praised the security partnership between the United States and Israeli militaries, and pledged the United States continued strong‎ support for Israel's security.
